[1] Spain ex Saudi Arabia, new case - MOH
Date: 6 Nov 2013
Source: MOH Spain [in Span. trans. by Mod.MPP]
http://www.msssi.gob.es/gabinete/notasPrensa.do?id=3081

Press Notes

Imported case of the new coronavirus detected in Spain

- The patient had travelled to Saudi Arabia
- The patient, who stayed in Saudi Arabia during the month of October [2013], is stable and in good condition
- The case does not present a public health risk in Spain
- The health authorities have followed national and international protocols for management of this case

[6 Nov 2013]
The Ministry of Health, Social Services and Equality has notified the detection of a laboratory confirmed imported case of the new coronavirus [MERS-CoV].

A female resident of Spain, born in Morocco, who had traveled to Saudi Arabia and who is currently admitted to the Puerta de Hierro Hospital in Mahadahonda (Madrid), where appropriate management of the case, including identification and evaluation of possible contacts of the case according to up-to-date protocols established between the Ministry and the CC AA [Autonomous Communities]

The patient, who returned to Spain on [1 Nov 2013], is in a favorable and stable condition [health wise]. Specimens analyzed in the National Microbiology Center were positive for infection with the new coronavirus [MERS-CoV].

The Ministry [of Health, Social Services and Equality] and the Community of Madrid are in the process of identifying all known close contacts of the patient, according to protocols recommended at the national and international level.

One imported case, in which all appropriate measures have been taken, does not pose a risk for the public health in Spain.

Following the established International Health Regulations, the Ministry of Health, Social Services and Equality has notified the World Health Organization as well as the European Rapid Alert Network (EWRS), with whom [the MOH of Spain] is maintaining close follow-up of the situation together with the Health Advisory Group of the Madrid Community.

The new coronavirus
The coronavirus responsible for the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome [MERS-CoV] was identified in Saudi Arabia in 2012. The majority of people affected by this virus present with an acute respiratory illness with symptoms of fever, cough and respiratory difficulties.

As of today [6 Nov 2013] there have been 150 confirmed cases reported, 125 of which have been in Saudi Arabia. All of the reported cases had association with 5 countries in the Middle East (Arabia, Jordan, United Arab Emirates, Qatar and Oman). In Europe cases have been reported, of whom were associated with importation from this zone, in 4 other countries: United Kingdom (2 cases), Germany (2 cases), France (1 case) and Italy (1 case).

